    <string name="more_details">Jahorina Ski Center, located in Bosnia and Herzegovina, is a top winter sports destination in the Balkans. Situated on Mount Jahorina near Sarajevo, it offers ski slopes for all skill levels, modern lifts, and facilities. Known for its role in the 1984 Winter Olympics, it now features over 40 kilometers of ski runs, snowboard parks, night skiing, and scenic trails for winter and summer activities. Jahorina also offers accommodations, restaurants, and wellness centers, making it popular with both thrill-seekers and families.</string>

