    <!-- Help center -->
    <string name="help_center_faq">FAQ</string>
    <string name="help">Help Center</string>
    <string name="help_center_question1">What activities are available at the Jahorina Ski Center besides skiing?</string>
    <string name="help_center_answer1">At Jahorina Ski Center, visitors can enjoy activities such as snowshoeing, sledding, scenic cable car rides, and relaxing at nearby bars and restaurants after a day on the slopes.</string>
    <string name="help_center_question2">Is there an option for night skiing?</string>
    <string name="help_center_answer2">Yes, night skiing is available on the Poljice slope at the Jahorina Ski Center from 6:00 PM to 9:00 PM, providing a unique evening experience on a well-lit trail.</string>
    <string name="help_center_question3">What should I do in case of an injury on the ski slopes?</string>
    <string name="help_center_answer3">In case of an injury, you are required to contact the mountain rescue service.
        They will intervene on the spot and transport you to the official medical facility at the ski resort. Contact number can be found under the useful information section.</string>
    <string name="help_center_question4">What are the operating hours of the ski resort during the ski season?</string>
    <string name="help_center_answer4">The ski resort operates from 9:00 AM to 4:00 PM during the ski season for daytime skiing, and also offers night time skiing from 6:00 PM to 9:00 PM.</string>

